Note:
Comprehensive Test Suite for GC Algorithms Module

Tests all functionality of the garbage collection algorithm implementations including:
- Mark-and-sweep, generational, incremental, and concurrent GC algorithms
- Memory allocation and collection performance optimization
- GC trigger mechanisms and heap management strategies
- Cross-generational reference handling and write barriers
- Parallel and concurrent garbage collection coordination
- Memory compaction and defragmentation algorithms
- GC statistics, metrics, and performance analysis
- Production-ready enterprise garbage collection scenarios
:End Note

Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/memory/gc_algorithms" as GCAlgorithms
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/utilities/common" as Common

Note: Test Configuration Constants
Let TEST_HEAP_SIZE be 1048576
Let TEST_ALLOCATION_COUNT be 100
Let TEST_GC_CYCLES be 10
Let TEST_OBJECT_SIZES be [16, 32, 64, 128, 256, 512, 1024]

Note: Test Result Tracking
Let test_results be Dictionary[String, Boolean] containing
Let test_count be 0
Let passed_count be 0
Let failed_count be 0

Note: Helper Functions for Testing

Process called "run_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Set test_count to test_count plus 1
    
    Try:
        Display message "Running test: " plus test_name
        Let result be test_function()
        
        If result:
            Set passed_count to passed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to true
            Display message "  ✓ PASS: " plus test_name
        Otherwise:
            Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to false
            Display message "  ✗ FAIL: " plus test_name
            
        Return result
        
    Catch error:
        Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
        Set test_results[test_name] to false
        Display message "  ✗ ERROR: " plus test_name plus " - " plus error.message
        Return false

Process called "assert_true" that takes condition as Boolean and message as String returns Boolean:
    If not condition:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_equal" that takes actual as Any and expected as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is not equal to expected:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_not_null" that takes value as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If value is null:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Return false
    Return true

Note: Unit Tests for Mark-and-Sweep GC

Process called "test_create_mark_and_sweep_gc" returns Boolean:
    Let gc_config be GCAlgorithms.GCConfig with:
        algorithm as "mark_and_sweep"
        heap_size as TEST_HEAP_SIZE
        trigger_threshold as 0.8
        
    Let gc be GCAlgorithms.create_mark_and_sweep_gc with config as gc_config
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as gc and message as "Mark-and-sweep GC should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as gc.algorithm_type and expected as "mark_and_sweep" and message as "Algorithm type should be set"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_mark_and_sweep_collection" returns Boolean:
    Let gc be GCAlgorithms.create_mark_and_sweep_gc with config as GCAlgorithms.default_config
    
    Note: Allocate objects
    Let allocated_objects be list containing
    For size in TEST_OBJECT_SIZES:
        Let obj be GCAlgorithms.allocate_object with gc as gc and size as size
        Let allocated_objects be allocated_objects with obj added
    
    Let pre_gc_stats be GCAlgorithms.get_gc_stats with gc as gc
    
    Note: Trigger collection
    Let collection_result be GCAlgorithms.collect with gc as gc
    
    Let post_gc_stats be GCAlgorithms.get_gc_stats with gc as gc
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as collection_result.success and message as "GC collection should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (post_gc_stats.collections_performed is greater than pre_gc_stats.collections_performed) and message as "Collection count should increase"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Unit Tests for Generational GC

Process called "test_create_generational_gc" returns Boolean:
    Let gc_config be GCAlgorithms.GenerationalConfig with:
        young_generation_size as TEST_HEAP_SIZE divided by 4
        old_generation_size as TEST_HEAP_SIZE multiplied by 3 divided by 4
        survival_threshold as 3
        
    Let gc be GCAlgorithms.create_generational_gc with config as gc_config
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as gc and message as "Generational GC should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as gc.algorithm_type and expected as "generational" and message as "Algorithm type should be set"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_generational_promotion" returns Boolean:
    Let gc be GCAlgorithms.create_generational_gc with config as GCAlgorithms.default_generational_config
    
    Note: Allocate long-lived objects
    Let long_lived_objects be list containing
    For i from 0 to 9:
        Let obj be GCAlgorithms.allocate_object with gc as gc and size as 128
        Let long_lived_objects be long_lived_objects with obj added
    
    Note: Perform multiple minor collections to trigger promotion
    For i from 0 to 4:
        GCAlgorithms.minor_collect with gc as gc
        
        Note: Allocate short-lived objects
        For j from 0 to 9:
            Let temp_obj be GCAlgorithms.allocate_object with gc as gc and size as 64
    
    Let generation_stats be GCAlgorithms.get_generation_stats with gc as gc
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (generation_stats.objects_promoted is greater than 0) and message as "Some objects should be promoted"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (generation_stats.old_generation_size is greater than 0) and message as "Old generation should contain objects"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Unit Tests for Incremental GC

Process called "test_create_incremental_gc" returns Boolean:
    Let gc_config be GCAlgorithms.IncrementalConfig with:
        time_slice_ms as 10
        yield_threshold as 1000
        interleaving_factor as 0.1
        
    Let gc be GCAlgorithms.create_incremental_gc with config as gc_config
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as gc and message as "Incremental GC should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as gc.algorithm_type and expected as "incremental" and message as "Algorithm type should be set"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_incremental_collection_timing" returns Boolean:
    Let gc be GCAlgorithms.create_incremental_gc with config as GCAlgorithms.default_incremental_config
    
    Note: Allocate objects to trigger incremental collection
    For i from 0 to 49:
        Let obj be GCAlgorithms.allocate_object with gc as gc and size as 256
    
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
    
    Note: Trigger incremental collection
    Let collection_result be GCAlgorithms.incremental_collect with gc as gc
    
    Let end_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
    Let collection_time_ms be end_time minus start_time
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as collection_result.success and message as "Incremental collection should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (collection_time_ms is less than 50.0) and message as "Incremental collection should be bounded in time"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Unit Tests for Concurrent GC

Process called "test_create_concurrent_gc" returns Boolean:
    Let gc_config be GCAlgorithms.ConcurrentConfig with:
        concurrent_threads as 2
        synchronization_points as 4
        barrier_type as "write_barrier"
        
    Let gc be GCAlgorithms.create_concurrent_gc with config as gc_config
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as gc and message as "Concurrent GC should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as gc.algorithm_type and expected as "concurrent" and message as "Algorithm type should be set"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_concurrent_collection_safety" returns Boolean:
    Let gc be GCAlgorithms.create_concurrent_gc with config as GCAlgorithms.default_concurrent_config
    
    Note: Start concurrent collection
    Let collection_handle be GCAlgorithms.start_concurrent_collection with gc as gc
    
    Note: Continue allocating during collection
    Let objects_during_gc be list containing
    For i from 0 to 19:
        Let obj be GCAlgorithms.allocate_object with gc as gc and size as 128
        Let objects_during_gc be objects_during_gc with obj added
    
    Note: Wait for collection to complete
    Let collection_result be GCAlgorithms.wait_for_collection with handle as collection_handle
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as collection_result.success and message as "Concurrent collection should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as objects_during_gc.length and expected as 20 and message as "Should be able to allocate during concurrent GC"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Performance Tests

Process called "test_gc_performance_comparison" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test different GC algorithms for performance
    Let algorithms be ["mark_and_sweep", "generational", "incremental", "concurrent"]
    Let performance_results be dictionary containing
    
    For algorithm in algorithms:
        Let gc be GCAlgorithms.create_gc with algorithm_type as algorithm and config as GCAlgorithms.default_config
        
        Let start_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
        
        Note: Perform allocation/collection cycle
        For i from 0 to (TEST_ALLOCATION_COUNT minus 1):
            Let obj be GCAlgorithms.allocate_object with gc as gc and size as 256
            
            If i modulo 20 is equal to 0:
                GCAlgorithms.collect with gc as gc
        
        Let end_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
        Let total_time be end_time minus start_time
        
        Set performance_results[algorithm] to total_time
    
    Note: All algorithms should complete in reasonable time
    For algorithm in algorithms:
        Let result be assert_true with condition as (performance_results[algorithm] is less than 1000.0) and message as (algorithm plus " should complete in reasonable time")
        
        If not result:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "test_memory_fragmentation_after_gc" returns Boolean:
    Let gc be GCAlgorithms.create_mark_and_sweep_gc with config as GCAlgorithms.default_config
    
    Note: Create fragmented allocation pattern
    Let objects be list containing
    For i from 0 to 19:
        Let size be (i modulo 3 plus 1) multiplied by 128
        Let obj be GCAlgorithms.allocate_object with gc as gc and size as size
        Let objects be objects with obj added
    
    Note: Free every other object to create fragmentation
    For i from 0 to 9:
        If i modulo 2 is equal to 0:
            GCAlgorithms.free_object with gc as gc and object as objects[i]
    
    Let pre_gc_fragmentation be GCAlgorithms.get_fragmentation_ratio with gc as gc
    
    Note: Trigger compacting collection
    GCAlgorithms.collect_with_compaction with gc as gc
    
    Let post_gc_fragmentation be GCAlgorithms.get_fragmentation_ratio with gc as gc
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (pre_gc_fragmentation is greater than 0.0) and message as "Should have fragmentation before GC"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (post_gc_fragmentation is less than pre_gc_fragmentation) and message as "Fragmentation should be reduced after compacting GC"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Error Handling Tests

Process called "test_gc_out_of_memory_handling" returns Boolean:
    Let small_config be GCAlgorithms.GCConfig with:
        algorithm as "mark_and_sweep"
        heap_size as 1024
        trigger_threshold as 0.9
        
    Let gc be GCAlgorithms.create_mark_and_sweep_gc with config as small_config
    
    Let allocation_failed be false
    
    Try:
        Note: Try to allocate more memory than available
        For i from 0 to 99:
            Let obj be GCAlgorithms.allocate_object with gc as gc and size as 512
    Catch error as GCAlgorithms.OutOfMemoryError:
        Set allocation_failed to true
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as allocation_failed and message as "Out of memory should be detected"
    
    Return result1

Process called "test_gc_corruption_detection" returns Boolean:
    Let gc be GCAlgorithms.create_mark_and_sweep_gc with config as GCAlgorithms.default_config
    
    Let obj be GCAlgorithms.allocate_object with gc as gc and size as 256
    
    Note: Simulate heap corruption
    GCAlgorithms.simulate_heap_corruption with gc as gc and object as obj
    
    Let corruption_detected be false
    
    Try:
        GCAlgorithms.collect with gc as gc
    Catch error as GCAlgorithms.HeapCorruptionError:
        Set corruption_detected to true
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as corruption_detected and message as "Heap corruption should be detected during collection"
    
    Return result1

Note: Integration Tests

Process called "test_end_to_end_gc_workflow" returns Boolean:
    Let gc be GCAlgorithms.create_generational_gc with config as GCAlgorithms.default_generational_config
    
    Note: Simulate realistic application workload
    Let live_objects be list containing
    Let temporary_objects be 0
    
    For cycle from 0 to (TEST_GC_CYCLES minus 1):
        Note: Allocate long-lived objects
        For i from 0 to 4:
            Let obj be GCAlgorithms.allocate_object with gc as gc and size as 512
            Let live_objects be live_objects with obj added
        
        Note: Allocate and immediately release short-lived objects
        For i from 0 to 19:
            Let temp_obj be GCAlgorithms.allocate_object with gc as gc and size as 128
            Set temporary_objects to temporary_objects plus 1
        
        Note: Trigger minor collection
        GCAlgorithms.minor_collect with gc as gc
        
        Note: Occasionally trigger major collection
        If cycle modulo 3 is equal to 0:
            GCAlgorithms.major_collect with gc as gc
    
    Let final_stats be GCAlgorithms.get_gc_stats with gc as gc
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (final_stats.minor_collections is greater than 0) and message as "Minor collections should occur"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (final_stats.major_collections is greater than 0) and message as "Major collections should occur"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (final_stats.objects_collected is greater than 0) and message as "Objects should be collected"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Test Runner

Process called "run_all_gc_algorithms_tests" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Display "Starting GC Algorithms comprehensive test suite..."
    
    Note: Mark-and-Sweep Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_create_mark_and_sweep_gc" and test_function as test_create_mark_and_sweep_gc
    run_test with test_name as "test_mark_and_sweep_collection" and test_function as test_mark_and_sweep_collection
    
    Note: Generational GC Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_create_generational_gc" and test_function as test_create_generational_gc
    run_test with test_name as "test_generational_promotion" and test_function as test_generational_promotion
    
    Note: Incremental GC Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_create_incremental_gc" and test_function as test_create_incremental_gc
    run_test with test_name as "test_incremental_collection_timing" and test_function as test_incremental_collection_timing
    
    Note: Concurrent GC Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_create_concurrent_gc" and test_function as test_create_concurrent_gc
    run_test with test_name as "test_concurrent_collection_safety" and test_function as test_concurrent_collection_safety
    
    Note: Performance Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_gc_performance_comparison" and test_function as test_gc_performance_comparison
    run_test with test_name as "test_memory_fragmentation_after_gc" and test_function as test_memory_fragmentation_after_gc
    
    Note: Error Handling Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_gc_out_of_memory_handling" and test_function as test_gc_out_of_memory_handling
    run_test with test_name as "test_gc_corruption_detection" and test_function as test_gc_corruption_detection
    
    Note: Integration Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_end_to_end_gc_workflow" and test_function as test_end_to_end_gc_workflow
    
    Display "GC Algorithms test suite completed."
    Display "Results: " plus passed_count plus " passed, " plus failed_count plus " failed, " plus test_count plus " total"
    
    Return Dictionary[String, Any] with:
        "total_tests" as test_count
        "passed_tests" as passed_count
        "failed_tests" as failed_count
        "success_rate" as (passed_count divided by test_count)
        "test_results" as test_results

Note: Main execution
Process called "main":
    Let results be run_all_gc_algorithms_tests()
    Return results

Note: Execute tests when module is run
Let main_result be main()